    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Table Width and Height"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The width and height of a table are defined by the width and height properties."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The example below sets the width of the table to 100%, and the height of the \n<th> elements to 70px:"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "data": [
        [
          "Firstname",
          "Lastname",
          "Savings"
        ],
        [
          "Peter",
          "Griffin",
          "$100"
        ],
        [
          "Lois",
          "Griffin",
          "$150"
        ],
        [
          "Joe",
          "Swanson",
          "$300"
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "table \n{\n  width: 100%;\n}\nth\n{\n  height: 70px;\n}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "To create a table that should only span half the page, use width: 50%:"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "data": [
        [
          "Firstname",
          "Lastname",
          "Savings"
        ],
        [
          "Peter",
          "Griffin",
          "$100"
        ],
        [
          "Lois",
          "Griffin",
          "$150"
        ],
        [
          "Joe",
          "Swanson",
          "$300"
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "table \n{\n  width: 50%;\n}"
        }
      ]
    },
